{"id":936,"date":"2023-09-21T15:53:20","date_gmt":"2023-09-21T15:53:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/aayushassociates.com\/food-social2\/recipe\/dilly-quick-pickles\/"},"modified":"2023-09-21T15:53:20","modified_gmt":"2023-09-21T15:53:20","slug":"dilly-quick-pickles","status":"publish","type":"recipe","link":"https:\/\/aayushassociates.com\/food-social2\/recipe\/dilly-quick-pickles\/","title":{"rendered":"Dilly Quick Pickles"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Pickles tend to be a love them or hate them food. I lean way into the love them camp \u2013 in all varieties. Pickled anything makes me happy, and now is the time of year when you can really explore. Carrots, radishes, beets. I pickle a lot of things, but there\u2019s nothing better than the classic. While you can add seasonings and mix up the styling of quick pickles, the key for me is starting with a 3-ingredient brine \u2013 equal parts water and white vinegar, plus kosher salt \u2013 to create the pickling liquid. The ratios are easily doubled or tripled for a larger batch. This one-cup to one-cup mix will generally create enough brine to fill at least three quart jars that have been tightly packed with veggies.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Pickles tend to be a love them or hate them food. I lean way into the love them camp \u2013 &hellip; <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":316,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","recipe-course":[94],"recipe-cuisine":[],"recipe-cooking-method":[],"recipe-tag":[],"recipe-key":[],"recipe-badge":[],"recipe-dietary":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/aayushassociates.com\/food-social2\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/recipe\/936"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/aayushassociates.com\/food-social2\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/recipe"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/aayushassociates.com\/food-social2\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/recipe"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/aayushassociates.com\/food-social2\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/us